<!-- Salary and job market questions -->
<category>
    <pattern>SALARY *</pattern>
    <template>
        Here's salary information for the major computing careers:
        
        **Software Developer:** $70,000 - $150,000+
        **Data Scientist:** $80,000 - $180,000+
        **Cybersecurity Specialist:** $75,000 - $160,000+
        **Web Developer:** $60,000 - $130,000+
        **Systems Admin/DevOps:** $60,000 - $150,000+
        
        Salaries vary significantly based on:
        • Experience level and skills
        • Geographic location
        • Company size and industry
        • Specific specializations
        
        For detailed salary info for a specific role, type the career name (e.g., "DATA SCIENTIST").
    </template>
</category>

<category>
    <pattern>JOB MARKET</pattern>
    <template>
        **Current Computing Job Market Outlook:**
        
        **Highest Growth Areas:**
        1. **Data Science** - 36% growth through 2031
        2. **Cybersecurity** - 35% growth through 2031
        3. **Full-stack Development** - 27% growth through 2031
        4. **Software Development** - 25% growth through 2031
        5. **DevOps Engineering** - 20%+ growth through 2031
        
        **Key Trends:**
        • Cloud computing skills in high demand
        • AI/Machine Learning expertise increasingly valuable
        • Cybersecurity critical across all industries
        • Remote work opportunities expanding
        • Emphasis on full-stack and versatile developers
        
        **Skills in Demand:**
        • Python, JavaScript, Java programming
        • Cloud platforms (AWS, Azure, Google Cloud)
        • Data analysis and visualization
