        • DevOps and automation tools
        
        Want specific information about career prospects in any field? Just type the career name!
    </template>
</category>

<!-- Skills and education questions -->
<category>
    <pattern>WHAT SKILLS *</pattern>
    <template>
        Skills needed vary by career path. Here's a quick overview:
        
        **Core CS Skills (All Careers):**
        • Programming fundamentals
        • Problem-solving and analytical thinking
        • Version control (Git)
        • Basic database knowledge
        
        **Career-Specific Skills:**
        • **Software Dev:** Multiple programming languages, frameworks, algorithms
        • **Data Science:** Statistics, Python/R, machine learning, data visualization
        • **Cybersecurity:** Network security, risk assessment, security tools
        • **Web Dev:** HTML/CSS/JavaScript, frameworks, responsive design
        • **Systems/DevOps:** Operating systems, cloud platforms, automation
        
        For detailed skill requirements, type a specific career name (e.g., "CYBERSECURITY").
    </template>
</category>

<category>
    <pattern>EDUCATION *</pattern>
    <template>
        **Education Requirements for Computing Careers:**
        
        **Minimum Requirement:** Bachelor's degree in Computer Science (which you're pursuing!)
        
        **Additional Education by Career:**
        
        **Software Developer:**
        • CS degree sufficient for most positions
        • Bootcamps accepted by some companies
        • Portfolio of projects often more important than advanced degrees
        
        **Data Scientist:**
        • Many positions prefer Master's degree
        • Strong math/statistics background essential
        • Certifications in specific tools valuable
        
        **Cybersecurity:**
        • CS degree plus security certifications
        • Certifications often required (Security+, CISSP)
        • Continuous learning due to evolving threats
        
        **Web Developer:**
        • CS degree helpful but not always required
        • Strong portfolio most important
        • Many successful self-taught developers
        
        **Systems/DevOps:**
        • CS degree plus cloud certifications
        • Hands-on experience highly valued
        • Vendor certifications important (AWS, Azure)
        
        Want specific education advice for a career? Type the career name!
    </template>
</category>

